headline: A Strange Gas-Pumping Defect Is Making $100,000 Corvettes Go Up in Flames
summary: Shawn Conner was refueling his high-end 2024 Corvette at a gas station in early June when the car spontaneously caught on fire, torching it in a matter of minutes.  Conner turned to a Facebook group of Corvette enthusiasts.  A video he posted showed the supercar exploding out of the blue, sending a person at a nearby gas pump scattering away.
